transcribe_handwriting.text:
This indenture made and entered into this 18th day of June
1832 bet[ween] Robert Green & Lucy his wife, Barton Hoone [Horne] Jr & Florence
his wife, Sanford Cockery & Elizabeth his wife, of the first part, and William Helton
of the County of Rappahannock & State of Virginia of the second part, witnesseth
that the said Robert Green & Lucy his wife, Woorsam Hoone [Horne] & Julietta Ann Hoone [Horne]
at present, & Elizabeth his wife, for and in consideration of the sum of four thousand,
five hundred & ninety-six 7/100$, by cash in hand paid by the said William Helton, the receipt
whereof is hereby acknowledged, have granted, bargained, and sold conveyed by these
presents, do grant, bargain, sell and convey unto the said William Helton, the later
now present, of [preconceived] certain tracts of land to a certain piece or parcel of land, containing
one thousand one hundred acres, more or less, being the tract of land, which was
equally by Jameson Bellaceate to the heirs of Wo. Hoone [Horne], before which
Elizabeth Hoone, widow of the said Wo. Hoone that the one [unclear] nine or three
she the said Elizabeth Hoone before the [?ions] estate, claiming by and during the said
interest hereby conveyed by the parties of the first part by their sound in the said
one half of the other [torn] remains same expression, to [torn] time is whole
upon the aforesaid right title interest, as well the present part of the [two]
[torn] the appurtenances thereto belonging, to have the said William Helton his heirs
onto assign, to the only proper rule at behoof, to the said William Helton
his heirs onto assign in science time the said Woorsan Froster [unclear] in science
William Helton, Julietta Ann Hoone, Sanford Cockery, and Elizabeth the
wife, for themselves their heirs, [assumer] & [invoice]. Each party agreeing
& saying, to have vital the said William Helton his heirs and [unclear] fore all
thesaid Robert Frenks & Lucy his wife, Woorsan Hoone [Horne] & [Julietta Anor], Florence
Sanford Cockery & Elizabeth his wife, the seen right, title & interest, in the
said tract or parcel of land, with the appurtenances thereto belonging, to unto
the said William Helton, his them cause interest and claim to assign the said
Robert Frenks and Lucy his wof, William and Julietta [unclear] the [debtors],
[orgy and] Elizabeth his wife, even express or present conveyance figuring,
day the 20th, Wo. Horne, Julietta Hoone [Horne], Sanford Cockery, & Elizabeth his wife,
thensaid assign them, under the penal year eight still design.

Robert Frenks
Lucy

William Hoone [Horne]
Julietta Ann Hoone [Horne]"
